7    Usable from Cython via::
8

11   This module provides Cython-level wrappers for all primary routines included
12   in LAPACK 3.4.0 except for ``zcgesv`` since its interface is not consistent

1523 # from ..linalg cimport cython_lapack

12023 # Python accessible wrappers for testing:
12024 
12025 def _test_dlamch(cmach):
12026     # This conversion is necessary to handle Python 3 strings.
12027     cmach_bytes = bytes(cmach)
12028     # Now that it is a bytes representation, a non-temporary variable
12029     # must be passed as a part of the function call.
12030     cdef char* cmach_char = cmach_bytes
12031     return dlamch(cmach_char)
12032 
12033 def _test_slamch(cmach):
12034     # This conversion is necessary to handle Python 3 strings.
12035     cmach_bytes = bytes(cmach)
12036     # Now that it is a bytes representation, a non-temporary variable
12037     # must be passed as a part of the function call.
12038     cdef char* cmach_char = cmach_bytes
12039     return slamch(cmach_char)
12040 
12041 cpdef double complex _test_zladiv(double complex zx, double complex zy) noexcept nogil:
12042     return zladiv(&zx, &zy)
12043 
12044 cpdef float complex _test_cladiv(float complex cx, float complex cy) noexcept nogil:
12045     return cladiv(&cx, &cy)
